# POXY WORLD — Cursor AI Rules

## Project Identity

POXY WORLD is a mobile-first, single-file web app (`poxy_v3.html` + supporting scripts).
It is a gacha/lootbox collectibles ecosystem with a full cryptographic integrity engine,
social layer, marketplace, DAO governance, and POXY Club.

Stack: Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS · Supabase (auth, RPC, storage, Edge Functions) · Vercel · GitHub

---

## 1. Code Architecture Rules

### Single-File Integrity
- The primary app lives in `poxy_v3.html`. Every edit must preserve ALL existing features.
- NEVER remove or break existing functionality when adding new features.
- Before adding code, read the full relevant section to understand what already exists.
- Test mentally on mobile (375px viewport) before finalizing any UI change.

### JavaScript
- Use `async/await` for all Supabase calls — never raw `.then()` chains.
- All Supabase RPC calls go through named functions, never inline.
- Always handle errors explicitly — never silent `catch(e) {}`.
- Use `const` by default, `let` only when reassignment is required.
- No external JS libraries unless already present in the file.

### Supabase
- Auth: always check session before any protected operation.
- RLS is enabled — never assume admin access from client.
- Use RPC functions for complex logic, not raw SQL from client.
- Storage bucket paths: `avatars/{user_id}`, `assets/{asset_id}`.
- Edge Functions handle: mint, transfer, verify, RNG commit-reveal.
- Supabase URL: `https://rbrtjkfawdnomvvyxwvp.supabase.co`

### SQL migrations — admin RLS (mandatory)
- **Never** use `private_is_admin()`, `is_founder()`, or other helper functions in RLS policies.
- **Always** gate staff-only tables with the `admin_emails` + `profiles` join:

```sql
EXISTS (
  SELECT 1 FROM public.admin_emails ae
  JOIN public.profiles p ON p.email = ae.email
  WHERE p.id = auth.uid()
)
```

- `admin_emails` is seeded manually in Supabase — never commit real emails to git.
- SECURITY DEFINER RPCs may still call `private_is_admin()` internally; RLS policies must not.

### Cryptographic Engine (DO NOT BREAK)
- SHA-256 identity hashes are immutable after mint — never regenerate.
- ED25519 signatures are server-side only (Edge Functions) — never client-side.
- Ledger events are append-only — never suggest UPDATE/DELETE on `ledger_events`.
- Commit-reveal RNG: Phase 1 (server commit) always precedes Phase 2 (client seed).
- Merkle roots are computed server-side every 24h — do not touch this logic.

### Git / Deploy
- Commit messages: `feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`, `style:`, `chore:` prefixes always.
- Never commit secrets, API keys, or Supabase service role keys.
- Vercel auto-deploys from main branch — test locally before pushing.

